Wifey: “I want a gyro” // Me: “I want pizza” 😏 So we found a @tazikis right next to a @jetspizza MEANT TO BE! 😜 Oh and we forgot to take a photo at tonight’s Christmas party, so here it is! 🎄 📸 Thanks @onerpm for a great evening and an awesome year!!!! 🎶 Lookin forward to the next!

Fam!! We’ve crossed 1M @spotify plays on “Sometimes Late At Night” 🤩 To my fans…I can’t thank y’all enough for the love! It truly means the world to me that so many of you relate to this song! I would like to thank my co-writers @tonywood_exit71 and @mattmcclurenashville (& Producer), my team @bowtosterngroup and distributor @onerpm for your constant support. Couldn’t have done it without y’all! 🙏 Most of all, I thank my wife @aimeeburgett for being the inspiration ❤️ You never cease to amaze me with who you are and everything you do. You’re my co-pilot, my world, my everything and I am beyond grateful to have you on this crazy adventure. It’s super cool to know that our first-dance song has meant so much to so many people and I can’t wait to see where it goes from here 😊.
.
.
.

You never know where life is gonna take you. Soak it all in. Enjoy the little things. Take the good, the bad, the in between, and have faith that you’re right where you’re meant to be. “Sometimes we hold the wheel, sometimes we’re in control…and sometimes nowhere roads know where to go.” I don’t know about you, but this year has shown me a LOT and I’m thankful for family, friends, and new fans along the way. May your new year be blessed with new beginnings, old friends, new friends, lots of good things, and strength to overcome anything thrown your way. Thank y’all for your continued support. A great big THANK YOU and a HAPPY NEW YEAR!

Fun story behind the music video! 🎶🎥 It takes place on 4 map dots! 😎 The wifey and I captured footage while we were on a WHIRLWIND of a trip around thanksgiving last year (You'll also notice some clips from our phone histories ;)...thankful for that lol)...So... We started in Maryville, NY --> Made our way to Toledo, OH ----> Stopped in my hometown of Latham, IL ---->> And ended up back home in Nashville, TN! Nothing like showing the "reel" story within a real story :) hope y'all enjoy it! Why love songs??? Well...in a thought out sentence, I say love is a powerful emotion and can overcome fear, sadness, anger, you name it... More simply put, you just can't go wrong with a love song :) Don't get me wrong...I love singin about havin a good time, throwin back some brewskis, raisin hell on the weekends, or even heartbreak, because we all go through it. 
.
.
But I think love is what the world needs most of right now, so I chose songs that represent a special part of my life...my wife, Aimee, who has been my rock, co-pilot, shotgun dreamer right alongside me. 
.
.
Maybe you're looking for love, getting married, celebrating 50 years, or standing by someone who's going through a rough patch. You'll find it in "Hey Maker." It means everything to have this project out in the world TODAY!! 
.
.
I say it a LOT, but I can't say it ENOUGH...Thank you for being on this ride with me and continuing to support all the new music. Y'all have a blessed day and we'll catch you soon!! (LINK TO STREAM "HEY MAKER" IN BIO) 🎶🤘.

Farm Focused takeover! @ericburgettmusic is taking over the Farm Focused accounts today as he travels to Omaha to perform! 

It all started with 88 keys!  Eric began performing on an old upright piano at his parents' tavern, The KORN KRIB, along with Sunday services at the Latham United Methodist Church. Growing up on a farm in Latham, Illinois, family, love, and hometown memories are the inspiration behind Eric’s music. 

Eric’s music has garnered over 11 Million streams and has been featured on editorial playlists including Spotify’s Wild Country, New Music Nashville, Next From Nashville, Country by the Grace of God, Young Nashville, Fresh Finds: Country, and Nashville Stripped; Apple’s New in Country, Country Faith, and Best New Songs feature list; Pandora’s New Country Now and Amazon’s Breakthrough Country as well as over 100k independent playlists.  Eric’s music videos have been featured on The Country Network and CMT.com. 

Originally written as his personal wedding song, Burgett’s latest radio single, “Sometimes Late At Night,” peaked at #26 on the Music Row CountryBreakout Chart,  also creating exposure on the Billboard Indicator chart.  Eric and his wife, Aimee, were married at The Country Music Hall of Fame in Nashville, where he surprised her with this song for their first dance. This release has become his most successful single to date, gaining over 2 Million streams. 
 
Eric has performed on The Kelly Clarkson Show, filmed at the Grand Ole Opry house, as part of a special tribute to CreatiVets.  Eric’s passion for helping veterans through music led to the release of “I’ll See You Again,” co-written and performed by Eric and released by Big Machine Label Group,  The single was featured on Spotify’s Veteran’s Day Country Compilation playlist and 9/11: Never Forget playlist.

Eric tours across the country and has opened shows for such artists as Chris Stapleton, Rodney Atkins, Lee Brice, Charlie Worsham, Phil Vassar, Clint Black, Jana Kramer, Craig Morgan, Jim Brickman, and the list goes on

💔 Last Friday, when we were blessed with the arrival of our baby boy, we received devastating news that one of our dear friends lost her life. My wife and I met Paizley Wilburn in January 2022, when she was cast as a dancer/actress in one of my music videos. 

I’ll never forget her bright smile and her heart of gold. She raved about how extra special it was to be a part of my music video and how she was a fan of my music, but little did she know, I was honored to have her be a part of it. When someone takes time out of their day to be a part of my musical journey…well…it truly means the world to me.

My heart breaks for Paizley’s family and all who knew her. 😇 Fly high, Paizley…I know you’re up there making the other angels dance with you and no doubt, heaven shines even brighter 🙏✝️ Hug your loved ones, call em, never stop praying for em, because life is so precious. 💔

THANK YOU @spotify for adding “Sometimes Late At Night - The Piano Version” to The New Music Friday Playlist! 🙏🤘 This song is super special and being a piano player, I just couldn’t resist putting out this version of it! 🎹 🎶 Most of y’all probably know the story behind it, but I wrote it for my wife as our first dance song!
